## Hierarchy (always)

1. **Common standards / enforcement** live only in **`repository-restructuring`** (`.cursor/rules`, pack, SSOT docs).  
2. **Consumers** ship a **thin root `AGENTS.md`** (template: pack **`templates/AGENTS.consumer.md`** or **`AGENTS.mssp-platform.md`**). Do **not** invent **`GROK.md`**.  
3. **`CLAUDE.md`** (if present) is a **thin adapter** (`@AGENTS.md`) â€” not a second standards master. Prefer pack **`templates/CLAUDE.md.adapter`**.  
4. **Models:** program default **`grok-4.5`**; long agentic / Build loops **`grok-build-0.1`** via **`.cursor/ai-gateway.json`** (xAI Docs MCP before changing ids).  
5. **Durable state** in git (**COMPREHENSIVE** Continue queue, CHANGELOG) â€” not chat history alone.

## Git + docs hygiene (always â€” Cursor and long loops)

**Operator standing order:** every substantive Cursor slice ends with **committed + pushed** git and **updated** SSOT/consumer docs (wiki re-ingest when docs move). Do **not** leave merge-ready work only on disk.

1. **Same change set:** code/script fix + `docs/CHANGELOG.md` + `COMPREHENSIVE` Current WIP (when status moves) + any touched runbook.  
2. **Commit:** `./scripts/git-commit-with-machine-lane.sh -m "â€¦"` (Machine-Lane trailer).  
3. **Push:** `safe-devops-wrapper git push` (or consumer PR when branch protection requires).  
4. **Cross-repo:** install pack / thin `AGENTS.md` on consumers when hierarchy rules change; no parallel `GROK.md`.  
5. **Canonical contract:** [CURSOR_AUTONOMOUS_LOOP_AND_PR_WORKFLOW_SSOT.md](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/docs/CURSOR_AUTONOMOUS_LOOP_AND_PR_WORKFLOW_SSOT.md) Â§5 + [ssot-doc-lifecycle-enforcement.mdc](ssot-doc-lifecycle-enforcement.mdc).

## Autonomous loops (no-HITL lanes)

Follow [CURSOR_AUTONOMOUS_LOOP_AND_PR_WORKFLOW_SSOT.md](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/docs/CURSOR_AUTONOMOUS_LOOP_AND_PR_WORKFLOW_SSOT.md):

- **Allowed:** docs/SSOT/wiki, fleet policy/AGENTS, local verify, scoped dep hygiene, code-reuse audits, PR slices.  
- **Forbidden without HITL:** token mint/revoke, deploy-token broaden, interactive `op signin` when no SA/Keychain, unguarded `wrangler deploy`/secrets, production DNS/Access cutover.  
- Every loop tick: research-first, gates before â€śdoneâ€ť, machine-lane commit trailer, **push**, no uncommitted merge-ready work.

## Cursor product features (use when helpful)

- **Side chats** (`/side`, `/btw`) for research/tangents without derailing the main agent.  
- **Agents Window transcript search** (Cmd+K) / in-thread Cmd+F â€” prefer over re-pasting full SSOT.  
